Using 200311192030, I tried to update all plugins by importing the latest plugins.
I got numerous exceptions. See the attached .log file.
This is a new problem.
It is really bad. As soon as this happens, the workspace seems to be corrupted.

The only way to fix it is to deleted the corresponding projects entries in:
D:\workspaces\head\plugins\.metadata\.plugins\org.eclipse.core.resources\.projects

Using latest M5 build, I got:

Replacing existing binary plugins with latest from build. I had to delete
manually the entry for org.eclipse.team.cvs.ssh in the .project folder in the
metadata.
I had to close Eclipse first.
*** This bug has been marked as a duplicate of 47267 ***

I don't understand how importing binary projects without using CVS could be a 
CVS problem.
